        "id": 1007145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-24T23:30:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "that sounds like it affects multiple hooks, not just this one.  so we should move this to setUp \u0026 tearDown in this class.\n\n```\ndef setUp...\n  ...\n  mock.patch.object(rh.git, \"find_repo_root\", side_effect\u003dmock_find_repo_root).start()\n\ndef tearDown...\n  mock.patch.stopall()\n```\n\nif you really wanted to scope it to this one test, then a decorator would be better rather than a with block that nests the entire body.  we do that many times in here already -- see testExpandVars as one example.",
      "parentUuid": "445d3276_3462837c",
